column5: One of my all-time favourite shows.
That was the very first show I ever watched on our first television in 1953. Ralph had his thumb stuck in a bottle.  Good stuff, Gary.
All the young lads are wondering what's so funny.... and who's Alice....
That show ruled! Almost as good as All in the Family... almost.
So... Wayne, you gonna tell us? Who is Alice? Alice Cooper? Was it one of his songs? Come on, this young buck has got to know....
And of course the real question is where did HE end up ?   God I think that show left me in tears and stitches more than an other
like ralph said  ONE OF THESE DAYS ALICE,POW RIGHT TO THE MOON.....THANKS FOR THE FUNNY PIC

we can't have a dancing girl as an avatar  but we can have a dead women that we know was in an abusive relationship from a husband that constantly verbally abused her and threatened her with physical violence  and by the looks of it made good on his threats  I guess I just don't understand the politically  correct thing

Reactment of Honeymooners doing Shakespeare -4:29 mins. http://youtube.com/watch?v=mgd-m749VHQ  Jackie Gleason-Hustler from 1961 with Paul Newman about high stake pool. Audrey Meadows-The Touch of Mink from 1962 with Gary Grant, Doris Day-comedy/romance  The show Honeymooners was a classic with alot of laughs.
This was totally lost on me....LOL.  Guess I'm too young to remember that one.  When I saw Alice, I thought Brady BUnch...LOL
You are not alone Terry.   I just dont get it, kinda sad really.
Alice Cooper is living the southwest and is quite the golfer. Joe
